g each person’s professional goals it means becoming part of a group that is the leader in its industry with an unrivaled global presence which reinvents itself every day to constantly rise to new challenges growth internationalization development of physical and digital retailing and more it means working in richly diverse teams and interlinking our stories with those of the brands whose rich heritage we represent as we perpetuate the future of tradition chantal gaemperle group executive vice president human resources and synergies read more key figures  employees  women  of employees outside france our talents share their experience claire smithwarner director of spirits education moët  hennessy françois guisnet director of production moët  chandon pauline monier intellectual property manager for internet louis vuitton mégane tschäpätt watchmaker at zenith tiffany stevenson sephora vp talent management  development rachel tan pei ling director of airport boutiques in singapore dfs anne picard coordinator for middle east and russia franchises céline daniel coutinho managing director of nowness jared bailey international spokesperson and global brow expert benefit cosmetics chloé cibulka environment manager for sites and stores lvmh all testimonials focus on a key métier production  supply chain technical development of products planning and optimizing of purchasing production and distribution according to the needs of the houses the production and supply chain métiers are essential in providing solutions to the strategic challenges faced by our group and meeting our customers expectations    louis vuitton malletier  mazen saggar immersion in situ take a glimpse at the daily lives of our employees   case studies find out how our employees respond to professional challenges in real situations   your career at lvmh recruitment to support the growth of our group we strive to attract and develop the most talented people around the world external recruitment is an essential source of fresh energy for the group and therefore it is a strategic pillar in our human resources policies  development building strong creative and passionate teams and developing their skills through ambitious training is a key priority which encompasses career management internal mobility training programs for highpotential managers and a proactive corporate social responsibility policy  view our job offers  follow us on linkedin  information by profile students young graduates managers experienced managers access your candidate space  search lvmhcom chargement close filter by sections group houses behind the scenes talents investors news  media business groups lvmh wines  spirits fashion  leather goods perfumes  cosmetics watches  jewelry selective retailing other activities pictures videos documents pages year of publication    month of publication liste des résultats chargement show more lvmh group  group approach governance and commitments  lvmh quick access go to menu go to menu go to content go to search by proceeding beyond this page you consent to the installation of cookies in order to provide interest based services and provide statistics to read more and manage your preferences click here lvmh €  en fr  it ja ru search menu group a familyrun group lvmh strives to ensure the longterm development of each of its houses in keeping with their identity their heritage and their expertise open the sharing menu facebook twitter linkedin google  email print increase font size decrease font size ecouter la page close share by email  champs obligatoires lvmh group  group approach governance and commitments  lvmh httpswwwlvmhcomgroup sender recipients multiple recipients separate the addresses with a comma message share the lvmh model “our model which is based on a longterm vision values the heritage of our houses and stimulates creativity and excellence it is the driving force for the group’s success and the guarantee of its future” bernard arnault ceo the lv