he dapifer reports that lvmh will gain ownership of christian dior haute couture leather both men’s and women’s readytowear and footwear lines  arnaults successful integration of various famous aspirational brands into a single group has inspired other luxury companies into doing the same thus the french conglomerate kering formerly named ppr and the swissbased richemont have also created extended portfolios of luxury brands the company is a component of the euro stoxx  stock market index contents  financial data  corporate structure  shareholders  subsidiaries  patronage  references  external links financial dataedit financial data in million euros           sales           net profit           total equity           during the first half of  lvmh recorded strong results in europe and united states the revenue of the groupe increased of  per cent corporate structureedit lvmh is based in  avenue foch in the th arrondissement paris france the company is listed on the euronext paris exchange and is a constituent of the cac  index as of  the group had revenues of € billion with a net income of just over € billion by the  february  the company had a share value of  million euros distributed in  shares in  with revenue of  billion lvmh is ranked first luxury goods company in deloittes global powers of luxury goods” report the group currently employs more than  people thirty percent of lvmhs staff work in france lvmh operates over  stores worldwide its current business plan aims to tightly control the brands it manages in order to maintain and heighten the perception of luxury relating to their products for example louis vuitton products are sold only through louis vuitton boutiques found in upmarket locations in wealthy cities or in concessions in other luxury goods shops such as harrods in london shareholdersedit at the end of  the only declared major shareholder in lvmh was groupe arnault the family holding company of bernard arnault the groups control amounted to  of lvmhs stock with  held through christian dior se and  held directly and  of its voting rights  by dior and  directly a further  of shares were declared as treasury stock with the remainder being free float lvmh holds  of the drinks division moët hennessy with the remaining  held by diageo subsidiariesedit a partial list including some of lvmhs bestknown brands and subsidiaries christian dior se wines and spirits ardbeg belvedere bodega numanthia cape mentelle chandon château cheval blanc château dyquem cloudy bay dom pérignon glenmorangie hennessy krug mercier moët  chandon newton vineyard ruinart terrazas de los andes veuve clicquot wenjun specialist retailing dfs le bon marché le grande epicerie sephora starboard cruise services fashion  leather goods berluti céline dior edun emilio pucci fendi givenchy kenzo loewe loro piana louis vuitton marc jacobs moynat nicholas kirkwood rimowa thomas pink watches  jewelry bulgari chaumet fred hublot tag heuer zenith perfumes  cosmetics acqua di parma benefit cosmetics fresh givenchy parfums guerlain kenzo parfums make up for ever parfums christian dior perfumes loewe maison francis kurkdjian conglomerates owned  christian dior make up for ever was established in  and was acquired by lvmh in  on  march  lvmh announced the acquisition of the  familyowned shares of the italian jeweller bulgari and the intention to make a tender offer for the rest which was publicly owned the transaction was about  billion in  lvmh invested  million in establishing lcapitalasia on  march  national business daily reported that midpriced clothing brand qda would open stores with the assistance of lvmh’s private equity lcapitalasia and the chinese apparel company xin hee co ltd in beijing in  lvmh invested  million in establishing lcapitalasia lvmh sales decreased by about  percent from in  in china and lvmh stopped opening stores in second and thirdtier cities in mainland china xue shengwen a senior researcher at chinaventure said the developing trend of the market is to take advantage of more acceptable prices in february  lvmh entered into a joint venture with the italian fashion brand marco de vincenzo taking a minority  stake in the firm patronageedit lvmh is a major patron of art in france the group supported about ten exhibitions as le grand monde d’andy warhol and picasso et les maîtres at le grand palais in paris lvmh also endorsed the patronage of l’atelier d’alberto giacometti and yves klein at centre georges pompidou since  when the lvmh flagship store opened in paris at  avenue george v  the company presented close collaboration with contemporary artists features included a light sculpture by american james turrell a metre  feet long travelling staircase showcasing the work of american video artist tim whitesobieski and an elevator linking the store to the top floor by icelands olafur eliasson in  gallery space was inaugurated on the second floor of the same building and named espace culturel icônes was one of the first exhibitions shigeru ban sylvie fleury zaha hadid bruno peinado andrée putman ugo rondinone james turrell tim whitesobieski and robert wilson were the nine artists invited by louis vuitton to participate in it in addition lvmh foundation created the young creators lvmh award an international competition opened to french and international beauxarts students each year six grants are allocated to the winners in november  lvmh created the lvmh young fashion designer prize which comes with a € grant with a year of mentoring and is the brainchild of delphine arnault the first winner will be chosen in  in february   finalist for the prize were shown in london such as simone rocha thomas tait meadham kirchhoff marquesalmeida j js lee and others in may  marquesalmeida was announced as the second winner lvmh underwrites other fashion competitions including the andam prize in france the international festival of fashion and photography in hyères france an investment fund for young designers created by the french ministry of culture and communication and a scholarship program and sponsored lecture theater at central saint martins in london the group also lends stradivarius violins to young talented musicians maxim vengerov and laurent korcia have used the instruments referencesedit  a b c d e f annual report  pdf lvmhcom retrieved  february    a b lvmh moët hennessy louis vuitton sa – company history funding universe retrieved  june    rachel sanderson in milan  march  retail  consumer – lvmh to take controlling stake in bulgari ftcom retrieved  june    lvmh group moet hennessy louis vuitton world leader in luxury listed on cac  index lvmhcom retrieved  june    the beginnings of château dyquem château dyquem retrieved  january   organizational chart as of april   dior archived from the original on  december  retrieved  april     bernard arnault cnn retrieved  may    lvmh subsidiaries brands and the  billion christian dior buy out  the dapifer the dapifer  retrieved    frankfurt stock exchange  a b c d a solid performance in a contrasting economic environment pdf lvmh retrieved  december    a b c annual report  pdf lvmhcom retrieved  february    singh prachi july   lvmh h revenues rise  percent fashionunited retrieved july     lvmh european equitites retrieved  december    deloitte global powers of luxury goods  report  a b lvmh first half  interim report lvmh retrieved  january   a b lvmh – reference document  pdf lvmh pp – archived from the original pdf on  may  retrieved  april    walsh dominic boyle catherine  april  lvmh denies being in mot sale talks with diageo the times london   financial documents lvmh   wellington elizabeth  mirror mirror joy make up for ever comes to king of prussia phillycom retrieved    dany sanz pionnière du makeup ellefr retrieved    roberts andrew  march  lvmh plans to buy bulgari for  billion after acquiring majority stake bloomberg retrieved  october    wendlandt astrid simpson ian  march  lvmh bags jeweller bulgari in  