ies jewelry perfumes spirits watches wines services department stores revenue €  billion  operating income € billion  profit € billion  total assets € billion  total equity € billion  owner christian dior se via financière jean goujon number of employees   subsidiaries list of subsidiaries website lvmhcom lvmh moët hennessy louis vuitton se better known as lvmh is a french multinational luxury goods conglomerate native of france and headquartered in paris the company was formed in  under the merger of fashion house louis vuitton with moet hennessy a company formed after the  merger between the champagne producer moët  chandon and hennessy the cognac manufacturer it controls around  subsidiaries that each manage a small number of prestigious brands the subsidiaries are often managed independently the oldest of the lvmh brands is wine producer château dyquem which dates its origins back to  christian dior the luxury goods group is the main holding company of lvmh owning  of its shares and  of its voting rights bernard arnault majority shareholder of dior is chairman of both companies and ceo of lvmhin  arnault purchased all the remaining christian dior shares in a reported  billion buy out the dapifer reports that lvmh will gain ownership of christian dior haute couture leather both men’s and women’s readytowear and footwear lines  arnaults successful integration of various famous aspirational brands into a single group has inspired other luxury companies into doing the same thus the french conglomerate kering formerly named ppr and the swissbased richemont have also created extended portfolios of luxury brands the company is a component of the euro stoxx  stock market index contents  financial data  corporate structure  shareholders  subsidiaries  patronage  references  external links financial dataedit financial data in million euros           sales           net profit           total equity           during the first half of  lvmh recorded strong results in europe and united states the revenue of the groupe increased of  per cent corporate structureedit lvmh is based in  avenue foch in the th arrondissement paris france the company is listed on the euronext paris exchange and is a constituent of the cac  index as of  the group had revenues of € billion with a net income of just over € billion by the  february  the company had a share value of  million euros distributed in  shares in  with revenue of  billion lvmh is ranked first luxury goods company in deloittes global powers of luxury goods” report the group currently employs more than  people thirty percent of lvmhs staff work in france lvmh operates over  stores worldwide its current business plan aims to tightly control the brands it manages in order to maintain and heighten the perception of luxury relating to their products for example louis vuitton products are sold only through louis vuitton boutiques found in upmarket locations in wealthy cities or in concessions in other luxury goods shops such as harrods in london shareholdersedit at the end of  the only declared major shareholder in lvmh was groupe arnault the family holding company of bernard arnault the groups control amounted to  of lvmhs stock with  held through christian dior se and  held directly and  of its voting rights  by dior and  directly a further  of shares were declared as treasury stock with the remainder being free float lvmh holds  of the drinks division moët hennessy with the remaining  held by diageo subsidiariesedit a partial list including some of lvmhs bestknown brands and subsidiaries christian dior se wines and spirits ardbeg belvedere bodega numanthia cape mentelle chandon château cheval blanc château dyquem cloudy bay dom pérignon glenmorangie hennessy krug mercier moët  chandon newton vineyard ruinart terrazas de los andes veuve clicquot wenjun specialist retailing dfs le bon marché le grande epicerie sephora starboard cruise services fashion  leather goods berluti céline dior edun emi